### Tested versions

4.4 stable

### System information

Godot v4.4.stable.mono - Windows 11 (build 26100) - Multi-window, 2 monitors - Vulkan (Forward+) - dedicated NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3060 Ti (NVIDIA; 32.0.15.6109) - 13th Gen Intel(R) Core(TM) i5-13600K (20 threads)

### Issue description

Jolt Physics and DEFAULT difference.
In Jolt 3D, when I use print to print print(result["face_index"]), the output value is -1.
When I use DEFAULTprint, the output is normal.
In 3D physics detection...

### Steps to reproduce

extends Node3D

@onready var camera_3d: Camera3D = $Camera3D
@onready var static_body_3d: StaticBody3D = $StaticBody3D
@onready var mesh_instance_3d: MeshInstance3D = $StaticBody3D/MeshInstance3D
@onready var collision_shape_3d: CollisionShape3D = $StaticBody3D/CollisionShape3D

func _process(_delta):
	if Input.is_action_just_pressed(&"mouse_left"):
		var mouse_position:Vector2 = get_viewport().get_mouse_position()
		var from:Vector3 = camera_3d.project_ray_origin(mouse_position)
		var to:Vector3 = from + camera_3d.project_ray_normal(mouse_position) * 100

		var query:PhysicsRayQueryParameters3D = PhysicsRayQueryParameters3D.create(from, to)
		var result:Dictionary = get_world_3d().direct_space_state.intersect_ray(query)

		print(result["position"])
		print(result["face_index"])

The problem only occurs when printing print(result["face_index"]).

